Animals (bears as well) often appear confused by mirrors due to a lack of self-recognition, interpreting their reflections as another animal, which can trigger curiosity, aggression, or social responses. Only a few species demonstrate the ability to recognize themselves, indicating a higher level of cognitive ability and self-awareness.
